WEBVTT

00:01.500 --> 00:03.168
Wow. That's...

00:03.235 --> 00:04.703
He can't carry these
on the bus.

00:04.770 --> 00:06.204
I'll drive him.

00:06.272 --> 00:09.074
Oh, hey, aiden would
real like to have
oatmeal cookies in his--

00:09.141 --> 00:10.508
Yeah, uh-uh.

00:10.576 --> 00:11.676
No. He's going
to be getting

00:11.744 --> 00:13.578
Lots of treats this week
trick or treating.

00:13.646 --> 00:15.747
Oh, hey, remember
I work a double today.

00:15.815 --> 00:17.515
Ok. I've got
plenty of Halloween
decorating to do.

00:17.583 --> 00:18.683
Hmm, that's always fun.

00:18.751 --> 00:21.186
oh!

00:21.254 --> 00:23.421
Hmm.
Hey, you cannot
wear a mask

00:23.489 --> 00:25.056
To school.

00:27.059 --> 00:29.761
Aiden, did you hear me?

00:29.829 --> 00:30.929
Ghouls don't talk.

00:30.997 --> 00:32.998
Oh, ok. Well, then nod.

00:33.065 --> 00:34.332
Ghouls' ears
don't work.

00:35.468 --> 00:37.702
They're decomposed.

00:37.770 --> 00:40.538
all right.

00:40.606 --> 00:42.340
How about you save
the costume for Halloween?

00:42.408 --> 00:44.042
Go on and get changed.
I'm going to take you
and your pumpkins to school.

00:45.611 --> 00:48.179
Ok, aiden, go.
I'll be up in
a minute to help.

00:48.247 --> 00:49.247
Ok, mom.

00:50.783 --> 00:54.019
Mia salter
says frogs are good
and toads are bad,

00:54.086 --> 00:56.554
But I like them both.

00:56.622 --> 00:59.424
And she repeats me
all the time.

00:59.492 --> 01:01.026
I hate that!

01:03.229 --> 01:07.265
It's not a bad word.
It's a feeling word.

01:07.333 --> 01:10.535
Fine, I won't say it.

01:10.603 --> 01:13.171
My mom says the same thing.

01:13.239 --> 01:14.806
Who do you think
is stronger?

01:14.874 --> 01:16.107
This guy,

01:16.175 --> 01:18.176
Or this guy?

01:18.244 --> 01:20.512
One time...
Ghosts?

01:20.579 --> 01:22.614
He's in there alone.

01:22.682 --> 01:24.282
Think it's maybe
some of those friends

01:24.350 --> 01:26.217
Who like to collect
shiny things?

01:26.285 --> 01:27.519
I have no idea.

01:27.586 --> 01:32.023
But this guy
has huge muscles,
and flying powers.

01:32.091 --> 01:33.925
I should probably
take him to school.

01:33.993 --> 01:36.027
I mean, maybe
the teacher knows
something about this.

01:36.095 --> 01:39.664
Wait a minute, he sees ghosts,
he feels what ghosts felt,

01:39.732 --> 01:41.833
But it's imaginary friends
you're worried about?

01:41.901 --> 01:43.802
Aiden doesn't have
imaginary friends.

01:43.869 --> 01:45.670
Uh, until now.

01:45.738 --> 01:48.340
It's normal.
He's normal.

01:48.407 --> 01:49.874
Gifted, but normal.

01:49.942 --> 01:52.277
Look, you're the one
who's going to be late
for the hospital.

01:52.345 --> 01:54.479
It's very nice
that you volunteered
for the blood drive,

01:54.547 --> 01:58.583
But you really belong
in a candy striper's outfit,

01:58.651 --> 01:59.818
You know that?

01:59.885 --> 02:01.453
Do candy stripers
still exist?

02:01.520 --> 02:03.588
Only in my wildest dreams.

02:05.658 --> 02:07.225
All right.
Bye.

02:07.293 --> 02:10.527
No, I haven't
seen aiden talking
to any imaginary friends.

02:10.596 --> 02:11.863
But I'll watch out
for it.

02:11.931 --> 02:13.131
It's good to find out
what kids are into.

02:13.199 --> 02:14.132
Thanks.

02:14.200 --> 02:16.768
Like his ghosts.

02:16.836 --> 02:19.270
You know,
he's an expert
on the topic.

02:19.338 --> 02:20.438
Oh.

02:20.506 --> 02:21.940
He's talked to you
about ghosts.

02:22.008 --> 02:23.575
Not me,
but I hear him

02:23.642 --> 02:25.477
Correcting
his friends, yeah.

02:25.544 --> 02:27.712
Don't worry.
All kids think

02:27.780 --> 02:30.382
They know everything
about something.

02:30.449 --> 02:33.251
I'm sure aiden will
chill on the topic
once the season's over.

02:38.357 --> 02:41.026
Is that too scary?

02:41.093 --> 02:43.395
He's seen worse.

02:43.462 --> 02:46.798
I know.
Some of the decorations
people put out...

02:46.866 --> 02:49.534
Hey, tahsa, let me see
what you're reading.

02:52.271 --> 02:53.705
Did your
older brother
give you this?

02:53.773 --> 02:56.341
Yeah.
I'm gonna keep it, ok?

02:56.409 --> 02:58.143
He's nine,

02:58.210 --> 02:59.411
Which is still
too young,

02:59.478 --> 03:01.012
In my opinion,
for this.
Yeah.

03:01.080 --> 03:03.314
Well, look,
you have your hands full,

03:03.382 --> 03:04.916
So thank you
for taking your time.

03:04.984 --> 03:07.585
Oh, aiden's a great kid,
and it's my job, so...

03:07.653 --> 03:09.387
Oh, speaking of which,

03:09.455 --> 03:11.656
I heard you own
the antique shop
in town.

03:11.724 --> 03:13.024
Yeah. Vintage, antiques.

03:13.092 --> 03:15.627
I have some things
maybe someone could use.

03:15.694 --> 03:17.429
Great. Drop them by anytime.
Ok.

03:17.496 --> 03:19.664
Thanks.

03:19.732 --> 03:22.834
ok.

03:22.902 --> 03:24.335
They can't kiss,
but can they say good-bye?

03:24.403 --> 03:26.471
Bye, mom.
Good-bye.

